\subsection{Response of Plants to Field Conditions}
\label{subsec:intro-resp-field}

Under field conditions, plants respond to the combination of stresses they naturally encounter, as
opposed to pre-determined combinations hypothesised to provoke a mechanism or response. Plants grown
in the field show markedly different phenotypes and responses to those grown in the lab. This
includes metabolic profiles \autocite{jankanpaa_metabolic_2012}, transcript abundances
\autocite{mishra_arabidopsis_2012, wituszynska_multivariate_2013}, photosynthetic differences
\autocite{mishra_arabidopsis_2012}, and survival and fecundity \autocite{kulheim_rapid_2002}.
